

# Tmux Mode States


[/] 1.) Client Key Table
[] 2.) Selection
[/] 3.) Pane Mode (copy-mode only)
[/] 4.) Pane Syncronized
[/] 5.) Window Zoomed
[/] 6.) Read-Only


# Modes that should fill the statusbar

1.) Client Key Table (except for root)
   - prefix (status-fill)
   - layout-mode (window-status)
   - resize-mode (pane-borders)
   - navigation-mode (status-fill)
   ...

2.) selection
3.) Pane Mode (except for normal copy-mode only)
   - copy-mode ()
     - clock-mode
   - view-mode (run-shell)
   -----------------
   - tree-mode (choose-tree)
   - buffer-mode (choose-buffer)
   - client-mode (choose-client)
4.) Pane Syncronized
5.) Window Zoomed
6.) Readonly

if pane is:
  zoomed, client-key-table, copy-mode, sync-on, readonly

  client-key-table, copy-mode


